Here is a multiple-choice question in JSON format.
{
    "question": "Consider the following Python code:\n```python\nnumbers = [10, 20, 30, 40, 50]\nresult = []\nfor i in range(len(numbers)):\n    if numbers[i] % 2 == 0:\n        numbers[i] /= 2\n        result.append(numbers[i])\n``` \nWhat will be the final content of the 'result' list after executing the code?",
    "choices": [
        {
            "choice": "[5, 10, 15, 20, 25]",
            "correct": "true"
        },
        {
            "choice": "[10, 20, 30, 40, 50]",
            "correct": "false"
        },
        {
            "choice": "[5, 10, 15]",
            "correct": "false"
        }
    ]
}

Are the distractors that are completely unique, or are they similar?
